<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Razamatazz;</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  What part of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  &quot;malicious deception and trickery&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is not a personal attack?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Krilen:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  What part is? Last I heard, personal refers to people, and people can be tricksters among other things, but people cannot be trickery. Besides that, it was malicious trickery.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> From <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.dictionary.com">www.dictionary.com</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> ma·li·cious adj. <br>
Having the nature of or resulting from malice; <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>deliberately</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> harmful; <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>spiteful</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->: malicious gossip.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->What part of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;dictionary&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> don't you understand?<br>
<br>
Only <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>people</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> have intent and motives.  You have stated, and restated, that it was <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Ylaine</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->'s intent to harm others by deceiving them, in other words, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Ylaine</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is a bad person who cannot be trusted.<br>
<br>
You do <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>not</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> refute her history, which I do not necessarily agree with, but dangle some supposed alternate history that you do not share with us.  <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>If</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> you were to refute her post, <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>then</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> you would counter the points made, and even share your <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;alternate history.&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Instead, you claim that <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Ylaine</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> deliberately intends harm to mages by deceiving them with her false world view.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> From <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.dictionary.com">www.dictionary.com</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  ad hom·i·nem adj. <br>
Appealing to personal considerations rather than to logic or reason: Debaters should avoid ad hominem arguments that question their opponents' motives.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->What part of <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>that</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> don't you understand?<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Krilen:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Anyway, not to put anyone down...<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->'nuff said.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Krilen:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  A good post SHOULD make people of the opposing view like me so busy with arguing the difference between fact...<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Agreed.  Where are your facts?  Where are your arguments?  Where is your much bandied but completely unseen alternate history?  All I see is your questioning of other people's motives, accusing other people of attacking you when you attack <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Ylaine</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, where exactly <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>are</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> your facts and arguments?  I know:<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Krilen:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  I can't even find time to actually come up with argument for the points made within the post.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->'nuff said.<br>
<br>
Put up or shut up.  Disagree or agree, point out new facts, propose alternative interpretations of event, show flaws in reasoning, but don't argue that <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Ylaine</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is purposely trying to hurt mages by lying to them.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Aamilae:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  but trods were not a necessary component to maintain our damage margin, which indicates that our offensive nature is slipping, wouldn't you think?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->No, this seems to be a complete non-sequitor.  Because we have been given an amazing tool, one of the most obvious applications of which is increasing our DPS in groups and raids, that therefore, our DPS is slipping?  What are you saying, that if we didn't have rods our damage output would suck, and therefore our damage output sucks?  Or potentially sucks?  Or trends towards suckage?  The situation as it is is that we do have rods, and they do in fact increase our our damage potential.  Of all the int casters, we are the <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>least</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> dependent on mana to do damage, we have the easiest time of replacing our mana, our damage output is less sensitive to downtime/uptime ratios, our sustained damage output is comparable to rogues and monks and what?  Our status as damage dealers is threatened somehow?<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Aamilae:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Your next argument will be we don't have to use trods to maintain DPS because we can canni pets.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Uhm...nopers....<br>
<br>
Not sure how you think you are able to read my mind, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Aamilae</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, but Mister Mathematics here would never be so stupid as to make some claim like that.  Rods are an important part of every 57+ mage's nutritious breakfast, along with pets, nukes, and so on.  I am well aware of the limitations of pet cannibalization, and especially for the epicked mage.  For many mages, non-epicked, and without healing support, it can be a very important tool.  But rods are obviously now a critical part of the mage class.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Aamilae:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  As you know though I put alot of love into my pets -- muzzle, armor, weapons.. my pet is important to me<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->As well you should know of me.  Until recently, I went through a couple a dozen gnoll hide lariats every week.  Up until <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Elemental Pact</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, I was all for making the best pet I could and keeping it alive.  When I get my epic, I no doubt will cherish it as you do.<br>
<br>
Really, I do not understand why you bring pet cannibalization into this, it has little to do with the subject at hand.<br>
<br>
All I am saying is that the mages have become in part a support class, that this support is viable in groups, and need not dominate a raiding magician's life unless there are insufficient numbers of mages available.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Aamilae:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Magicians on a raid change their major/minors quite a bit. We will typically minor in damage, pets and major in utility.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Well, I think that's the problem, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Aamilae</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  Yes, mages provide some unique support capacities, and therefore, if there is only one mage on the raid capable of providing that support, guess what?  Their time is spent providing support and damage dealing, of which there is likely an excess anyway, fades into the background.<br>
<br>
The problem appears to me to be that you do not have enough magicians.  Of course one magician is stressed and has to focus on support.  Get three, and the picture will be <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>very</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> different.  Using your own terminology, each mage can then <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;minor&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> in support, and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;major&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> in damage.  The flaw is not with the class, but with an insufficient number of mages.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Wisbus:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  ...some guilds recruit only mages for mod rods. That?s not the mages fault, or the mage class in general - it's the guilds.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Exactly.  My guild has a strong mage presence, and I make a point of cultivating relationships with other mages by helping on their epics and making pet groups and so on, so I am rarely the only mage on a raid, even if I am short on guildies.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Wilbus:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Glad I'm a mage!<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Yeppers, never wanted to be anything else.  What's an alt?<br>
